From Ajjanghthi thaya Adheva, hata Jagge Gurushishya ev;
Yaksha Raksha je Ajje Upavya, Pachha Tehe Mali Khava Aavya.

To: God is from above, was in this world a guru and disciple; The Yaksha protected what was left, then it came back to eat.

Empty space is the word in context, air is touch; 
That very form and taste, then it sees, 
the earth smelling it.

Here is the translation:

That's when all happiness ended, being with others; 
The Supreme Being is evident only when one does not take actions that are to be done.

Here is the translation:

That great power is beyond measure, you have made this war known; 
He then knows the joys and sorrows of men, not to be narrated in this story.
